description.plain:
Jayvon Lanell May (b. August 2, 1999), better known by his stage name Ambjaay, is a rapper hailing from Los Angeles. He is known for his breakout single “Uno,” which would be remixed by Lil Pump and Tyga and lead him to a record deal with Columbia Records.

On February 14, 2019, Jaay would release his debut EP, It Cost to Live Like This.

songs.title: Uno

description.plain: Released on May 10, 2019, this song is by Los Angeles native rapper Ambjaay. It peaked at #82 on the charts in the United States. The song and Ambjaay also gained the attention of big names, with Wiz Khalifa, Kaloney, and Chris Brown all showing interest on social media. Wiz Khalifa even replying to him on Twitter, Ambjaay says.
